.:: Puzzle 6x2-Level-3-3::.
2 different brands of cigars are smoked: dunhill, davidoff
There 2 different types of food: apple, avocado
House: art-deco, cape-cod
The people have 2 different jobs:  coach, scientist
The people use 2 different means of transport: van, taxi
2 different pets are kept: hedgehog, lizard
1. the person eating apple is on the right of the person eating avocado##1
2. the art-deco house is on the left or right of the owner of the lizard##3
3. the scientist is on the left of the owner of the hedgehog##1
4. the davidoff-smoker is on the left of the person driving the van##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |      2      |
| Cigar      | davidoff    | dunhill      |
| Food         | avocado | apple     |
| House   | cape-cod      | art-deco |
| Job   | scientist      | coach       |
| Transport   | taxi  | van     |
| Pet         | lizard      | hedgehog    |

